<inglise> Commission Regulation (EC) No 1510/2001 of 24 July 2001 amending Regulation (EC) No 1047/2001 introducing a system of import licences and certificates of origin and establishing the method for managing tariff quotas for garlic imported from third countries </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1510/2001, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1047/2001, millega kehtestatakse impordilitsentside ja p&auml;ritolusertifikaatide s&uuml;steem ja kolmandatest riikidest imporditava k&uuml;&uuml;slaugu tariifikvootide haldamise meetod </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2200/96 of 28 October 1996 on the common organisation of the market in fruit and vegetables(1), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 911/2001(2), and in particular Article 31(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 28. oktoobri 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2200/96 puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 911/2001, (2) eriti selle artikli 31 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Article 4(2) of Commission Regulation (EC) No 1047/2001(3) lays down the conditions under which applications for import licences for garlic may be lodged, and the maximum quantity that each application may cover. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1047/2001 (3) artikli 4 l&otilde;ikega 2 kehtestatakse k&uuml;&uuml;slaugu impordilitsentside taotlemise tingimused ja suurim kogus, mida iga taotlus v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitleda; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) In order to facilitate trade and to stabilise the market, the maximum quantity of each application from traditional importers lodged every quarter for imports of garlic from a specific origin should be fixed on the basis of the annual imports previously made by those importers from that same origin rather than on the basis of the maximum quantity available. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) kaubanduse h&otilde;lbustamiseks ja turu stabiliseerimiseks tuleks kindla p&auml;ritoluga k&uuml;&uuml;slaugu importimiseks iga seniste importijate igal kvartalil esitatava taotlusega h&otilde;lmatav maksimumkogus kinnitada pigem sama p&auml;ritoluga k&uuml;&uuml;slaugu koguse p&otilde;hjal, mis need importijad on varem aastas importinud, kui saadaoleva maksimumkoguse p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Fresh Fruit and Vegetables, </inglise>
<eesti> 3) k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on v&auml;rske puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;givilja turu korralduskomitee arvamusega koosk&otilde;las, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>

<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1047/2001 artikli 4 l&otilde;ige 2 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4(2) of Regulation (EC) No 1047/2001 is replaced by the following: "2. For each of the three origins and for each of the quarters indicated in Annex I, an operator may not lodge more than four applications for A licences for the import of garlic and the applications must be at least five days apart. </inglise>
<eesti> "2. Ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib iga I lisas nimetatud kolme p&auml;ritolu ja iga kvartali puhul esitada k&otilde;ige rohkem neli A-litsentsi taotlust k&uuml;&uuml;slaugu importimiseks ning taotluste esitamise vahe peab olema v&auml;hemalt viis p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) each application from a traditional importer within the meaning of Article 6(3) may cover no more than the maximum level of his imports for that quarter in the preceding three calendar years; </inglise>
<eesti> a) peab artikli 6 l&otilde;ikes 3 m&auml;&auml;ratletud senise importija iga taotlus piirduma maksimumkogusega, mis ta on importinud eelnenud kolme kalendriaasta asjakohases kvartalis; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) each application from a new importer within the meaning of Article 6(4) may cover no more than 10 % of the quantity indicated in Annex I for that origin and that quarter. </inglise>
<eesti> b) peab artikli 6 l&otilde;ikes 4 m&auml;&auml;ratletud uue importija iga taotlus piirduma k&otilde;ige rohkem 10%ga I lisas asjakohase p&auml;ritolu ja kvartali kohta esitatud kogusest. </eesti>
<inglise> The applications for A licences shall be accompanied by information allowing the competent national authorities to verify to their satisfaction that the provisions of this paragraph have been complied with." </inglise>
<eesti> A-litsentsi taotlustele lisatakse teave, mis v&otilde;imaldab p&auml;devaid riigiasutusi rahuldaval viisil kinnitada k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike s&auml;tete t&auml;itmist." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
